  7,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m-ŠĻĘ√£d
  7,2,"ňĻThis isňļ a Book sent down to you ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒdo not let anxiety into your heart regarding it‚ÄĒso with it you may warn ňĻthe disbelieversňļ, and as a reminder to the believers"
  7,3,"Follow what has been sent down to you from your Lord, and do not take others as guardians besides Him. How seldom are you mindful"
  7,4,ňĻImagineňļ how many societies We have destroyed! Our torment took them by surprise ňĻwhile sleepingňļ at night or midday
  7,5,"Their only cry‚ÄĒwhen overwhelmed by Our torment‚ÄĒwas, ‚ÄúWe have indeed been wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  7,6,We will surely question those who received messengers and We will question the messengers ňĻthemselvesňļ
  7,7,Then We will give them a full account with sure knowledge‚ÄĒfor We were never absent
  7,8,"The weighing on that Day will be just. As for those whose scale will be heavy ňĻwith good deedsňļ, ňĻonlyňļ they will be successful"
  7,9,"But those whose scale is light, they have doomed themselves for wrongfully denying Our signs"
  7,10,We have indeed established you on earth and provided you with a means of livelihood. ňĻYetňļ you seldom give any thanks
  7,11,"Surely We created you,¬†then shaped you, then said to the angels, ‚ÄúProstrate before Adam,‚ÄĚ so they all did‚ÄĒbut not Ibl√ģs,¬†who refused to prostrate with the others"
  7,12,"God asked, ‚ÄúWhat prevented you from prostrating when I commanded you?‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.‚ÄĚ"
  7,13,"God said, ‚ÄúThen get down from Paradise! It is not for you to be arrogant here. So get out! You are truly one of the disgraced.‚ÄĚ"
  7,14,"He appealed, ‚ÄúThen delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.‚ÄĚ"
  7,15,"God said, ‚ÄúYou are delayed ňĻuntil the appointed Dayňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  7,16,"He said, ‚ÄúFor leaving me to stray I will lie in ambush for them on Your Straight Path"
  7,17,"I will approach them from their front, their back, their right, their left, and then You will find most of them ungrateful.‚ÄĚ"
  7,18,"God said, ‚ÄúGet out of Paradise! You are disgraced and rejected! I will certainly fill up Hell with you and your followers all together.‚ÄĚ"
  7,19,"ňĻGod said,ňļ ‚ÄúO Adam! Live with your wife in Paradise and eat from wherever you please, but do not approach this tree, or else you will be wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  7,20,"Then Satan tempted them in order to expose what was hidden of their nakedness. He said, ‚ÄúYour Lord has forbidden this tree to you only to prevent you from becoming angels or immortals.‚ÄĚ"
  7,21,"And he swore to them, ‚ÄúI am truly your sincere advisor.‚ÄĚ"
  7,22,"So he brought about their fall through deception. And when they tasted of the tree, their nakedness was exposed to them, prompting them to cover themselves with leaves from Paradise. Then their Lord called out to them, ‚ÄúDid I not forbid you from that tree and ňĻdid I notňļ tell you that Satan is your sworn enemy?‚ÄĚ"
  7,23,"They replied, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We have wronged ourselves. If You do not forgive us and have mercy on us, we will certainly be losers.‚ÄĚ"
  7,24,"God said, ‚ÄúDescend as enemies to each other.¬†You will find in the earth a residence and provision for your appointed stay.‚ÄĚ"
  7,25,"He added, ‚ÄúThere you will live, there you will die, and from there you will be resurrected.‚ÄĚ"
  7,26,"O children of Adam! We have provided for you clothing to cover your nakedness and as an adornment. However, the best clothing is righteousness. This is one of God‚Äôs bounties, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  7,27,O children of Adam! Do not let Satan deceive you as he tempted your parents out of Paradise and caused their cover to be removed in order to expose their nakedness. Surely he and his soldiers watch you from where you cannot see them. We have made the devils allies of those who disbelieve
  7,28,"Whenever they commit a shameful deed,¬†they say, ‚ÄúWe found our forefathers doing it and God has commanded us to do it.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúNo! God never commands what is shameful. How can you attribute to God what you do not know?‚ÄĚ"
  7,29,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúMy Lord has commanded uprightness and dedication ňĻto Him aloneňļ in worship, calling upon Him with sincere devotion. Just as He first brought you into being, you will be brought to life again.‚ÄĚ"
  7,30,"He has guided some, while others are destined to stray. They have taken devils as their masters instead of God‚ÄĒthinking they are ňĻrightlyňļ guided"